@startuml apply

' Apply is the deploy path. It opens from the shared pipeline (drawn in
' pipeline.puml), lands the Host Scaffold across the host's installation
' contracts, then primes the Contributor Foundations through the just-installed
' Facade (""vv prime"") so spawn/fork resolve durably on the Host. It is subject
' to the Pristine guard: Apply refuses any Session Clone the operator hot-fixed
' since Clone, so the Host only ever reflects reviewed, merged code.

!include elements.puml

title Ringmaster — Apply (deploy path)

left to right direction

actor "David" as david

rectangle "Pipeline\n(Assemble → Build → Install)" as pipeline <<phase>>
rectangle "Prime"                                  as prime    <<phase>>

david    --> pipeline : ""ringmaster apply""
pipeline --> host     : place Skills, Data Files,\nHooks, settings.json
host     --> prime    : prime Foundations\nvia installed ""vv prime""
prime    --> claude   : drive priming turns

' Drop UL elements declared in elements.puml but not referenced here, so the
' rendered SVG carries no orphan boxes.
remove @unlinked

@enduml
